OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F407A1774530670
OL,3,CResidents concerned about financial
OL,4,Cburden of cladding crisis
OL,6,FResidents who were left homeless by a
OL,7,Ffire in their block say they feel
OL,8,Fbetrayed by the government who are
OL,9,Fasking for the money that was paid
OL,10,Ftowards fixing their cladding.
OL,12,FThe Spectrum Building in Dagenham
OL,13,Fcaught fire in August 2024.
OL,15,FThere were 45 fire engines and over
OL,16,F200 firefighters at the scene on the
OL,17,Fnight of the fire - more than 100
OL,18,Fpeople were evacuated.
OL,20,FThe building was demolished in
OL,21,FDecember 2024.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G1/9
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,408,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40702
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F407A1774530670
OL,3,CResidents concerned about financial
OL,4,Cburden of cladding crisis
OL,6,FHowever, residents have revealed that
OL,7,Fthe government wants six million
OL,8,Fpounds after the company responsible
OL,9,Ffor removing the cladding went bust.
OL,11,FGovernment policy currently says: "If
OL,12,Fyou are a qualifying leaseholder, you
OL,13,Fwill be completely protected from all
OL,14,Fcosts related to the remediation of
OL,15,Funsafe cladding systems. If you are a
OL,16,Fnon-qualifying leaseholder, you will
OL,17,Fbe fully protected where your building
OL,18,Fowner is - or is related to - the
OL,19,Fdeveloper that was responsible for the
OL,20,Fdefects."
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G2/9
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,408,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40703
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F407A1774530670
OL,3,CResidents concerned about financial
OL,4,Cburden of cladding crisis
OL,6,FFollowing the Grenfell Tower Fire, the
OL,7,Fbuilding was discovered to have non-
OL,8,Fcompliant cladding with the London
OL,9,FFire Brigade also flagging safety
OL,10,Fissues and a resulting enforcement
OL,11,Fnotice to the building management just
OL,12,Fover a year before the fire.
OL,14,FThe Building Safety Fund was developed
OL,15,Fto fund the remediation costs.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G3/9
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,408,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40704
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F407A1774530670
OL,3,CResidents concerned about financial
OL,4,Cburden of cladding crisis
OL,6,FBut there are now concerns that the
OL,7,Fland could be sold to pay these costs
OL,8,Fwhich means leaseholders and owners
OL,9,Fcould lose money that would be put
OL,10,Ftowards finding themselves new homes
OL,11,Fas it's paid back to the government.
OL,13,FSarah Williams is a former resident
OL,14,Fand leaseholder at the building.
OL,16,F"The government is asking for money
OL,17,Fback and that money is money for my
OL,18,Fhome," she explained.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G4/9
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,408,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40705
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F407A1774530670
OL,3,CResidents concerned about financial
OL,4,Cburden of cladding crisis
OL,6,F"And for my future. And I think it
OL,7,Fdoesn't make sense that they are
OL,8,Ftrying to get that money back now. The
OL,9,Fbuilding does not exist."
OL,11,FFor many residents, the money that is
OL,12,Fin the land of the burnt down building
OL,13,Fcould help them get a new home.
OL,15,FSarah is still paying the mortgage for
OL,16,Fthe flat that doesn't exist and says
OL,17,Fthis is just an extra stress.
OL,19,F"It could be the difference between
OL,20,Fbuying a house and not buying a house"
OL,21,Fshe explained.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G5/9
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,408,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40706
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F407A1774530670
OL,3,CResidents concerned about financial
OL,4,Cburden of cladding crisis
OL,6,F"I didn't have to pay for the cladding
OL,7,Fto be fixed, so why should I have to
OL,8,Fpay the government money back now? It
OL,9,Fmakes no sense."
OL,11,FAngela Rayner, who was then the
OL,12,FHousing Minister, visited the
OL,13,Fresidents after the fire.
OL,15,FBut she also tweeted about the costs
OL,16,Fof cladding remediation in 2021.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G6/9
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,408,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40707
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F407A1774530670
OL,3,CResidents concerned about financial
OL,4,Cburden of cladding crisis
OL,6,FShe said: "Leaseholders should not and
OL,7,Fmust not pay for the cladding crisis
OL,8,Fthat was caused by dodgy developers,
OL,9,Fcowboy builders and manufacturers of
OL,10,Fflammable cladding.
OL,12,F"They should pay the costs, not
OL,13,Fresidents who bought their homes in
OL,14,Fgood faith and have been left in this
OL,15,Fsituation."
OL,17,FThis leaves these residents feeling
OL,18,Flet down.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G7/9
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,408,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40708
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F407A1774530670
OL,3,CResidents concerned about financial
OL,4,Cburden of cladding crisis
OL,6,F"I feel betrayed. I thought the
OL,7,Fgovernment had promised to protect
OL,8,Fleaseholders and now the government is
OL,9,Ftrying to ruin my future. I feel
OL,10,Fbetrayed," said Sarah.
OL,12,F"I just want the government to change
OL,13,Fits mind. The government could decide
OL,14,Ftoday to not try and claim this money
OL,15,Fback. I just want them to reverse that
OL,16,Fdecision."
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G8/9
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
